theorem Topology.interior_union_three_subset {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B C : Set X} :
    interior (A : Set X) ∪ interior B ∪ interior C ⊆
      interior (A ∪ B ∪ C : Set X) := by
  intro x hx
  -- Analyse the membership of `x` in the triple union.
  cases hx with
  | inl hAB =>
      -- `x ∈ interior A ∪ interior B`
      cases hAB with
      | inl hA =>
          -- Case `x ∈ interior A`
          have h_subset : (A : Set X) ⊆ A ∪ B ∪ C := by
            intro y hy; exact Or.inl hy
          have h_int : (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆ interior (A ∪ B ∪ C) :=
            interior_mono h_subset
          exact h_int hA
      | inr hB =>
          -- Case `x ∈ interior B`
          have h_subset : (B : Set X) ⊆ A ∪ B ∪ C := by
            intro y hy; exact Or.inr (Or.inl hy)
          have h_int : (interior (B : Set X)) ⊆ interior (A ∪ B ∪ C) :=
            interior_mono h_subset
          exact h_int hB
  | inr hC =>
      -- Case `x ∈ interior C`
      have h_subset : (C : Set X) ⊆ A ∪ B ∪ C := by
        intro y hy; exact Or.inr (Or.inr hy)
      have h_int : (interior (C : Set X)) ⊆ interior (A ∪ B ∪ C) :=
        interior_mono h_subset
      exact h_int hC

theorem Topology.closure_interior_union_three_subset
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B C : Set X} :
    closure (interior (A : Set X)) ∪ closure (interior B) ∪ closure (interior C) ⊆
      closure (interior (A ∪ B ∪ C : Set X)) := by
  intro x hx
  --  We analyse the membership of `x` in the triple union.
  cases hx with
  | inl hxAB =>
      --  `x` lies in the union of the first two closures.
      cases hxAB with
      | inl hxA =>
          --  Case `x ∈ closure (interior A)`
          have h_sub :
              closure (interior (A : Set X)) ⊆
                closure (interior (A ∪ B ∪ C : Set X)) := by
            --  Use monotonicity with the obvious inclusion `A ⊆ A ∪ B ∪ C`.
            have h_inc : (A : Set X) ⊆ A ∪ B ∪ C := by
              intro y hy
              exact Or.inl <| Or.inl hy
            exact
              Topology.closure_interior_mono
                (X := X) (A := A) (B := A ∪ B ∪ C) h_inc
          exact h_sub hxA
      | inr hxB =>
          --  Case `x ∈ closure (interior B)`
          have h_sub :
              closure (interior (B : Set X)) ⊆
                closure (interior (A ∪ B ∪ C : Set X)) := by
            have h_inc : (B : Set X) ⊆ A ∪ B ∪ C := by
              intro y hy
              exact Or.inl <| Or.inr hy
            exact
              Topology.closure_interior_mono
                (X := X) (A := B) (B := A ∪ B ∪ C) h_inc
          exact h_sub hxB
  | inr hxC =>
      --  Case `x ∈ closure (interior C)`
      have h_sub :
          closure (interior (C : Set X)) ⊆
            closure (interior (A ∪ B ∪ C : Set X)) := by
        have h_inc : (C : Set X) ⊆ A ∪ B ∪ C := by
          intro y hy
          exact Or.inr hy
        exact
          Topology.closure_interior_mono
            (X := X) (A := C) (B := A ∪ B ∪ C) h_inc
      exact h_sub hxC

theorem Topology.closure_idempotent {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    closure (closure (A : Set X)) = closure A := by
  simpa [closure_closure]
